> Quick question for the custom guys:
>
> Is anyone running a Berg bus shifter?
>
> >These have a super duty 5/8" shifter shaft that is extremely strong and
are
> warranted for one year against breakage. Reduces original travel by about
> 35%, 4" longer and about 4" closer to the driver. No more reaching for the
> shifter. All have standard 21.50mm ball for 1960 and later buses.
Originated
> by Gene Berg in 1978. Made in USA by Gene Berg Enterprises. SW 9# <
>
> >GB 6750 66-79 bus shifter. Fits chassis number 216-028-112 to the Vanagon
>
> I figure it might be time to clean up that vague and sloppy shifting in
